media.altText:
So New Zealand PM stepped down citing burnout. 
It's important to remember that no one amongst us is immune to burnout. It's so important to do things other than work (fun things) in our daily routine to prevent burnout. And yes, working incessantly for months, and then taking a 5-day break rarely works, and it's definitely not a substitute for a more balanced lifestyle.

If you are a person who wants to achieve a lot, you will have to remain productive for a long duration, and that can happen only if you give your body & mind regular opportunities to recuperate. 
This note is as much for you as it's for me.
